The bug in the code is that even if an event is not approved, it still gets
gets assigned to lastApproved which results in the id of that unapproved ev
event being considered as the last approved one. 

To fix this issue we need to add a condition inside the for loop so that it
it only updates the lastApproved variable when an event is both present and
and approved:

```tundra
val events = [
   { id: "A", approved: true },
   { id: "B", approved: true },
   { id: "C", approved: false }
];

var lastApproved = "none";
for (event in events) {
  if(event.approved == true){
    lastApproved = event.id;
  }
}
print(lastApproved);
```
With this modification, the program correctly identifies that B is the last
last approved event and prints "B" when run.
